#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:10
msgid "2.3 Hebbian Learning as Sculpting Energy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:12
msgid ""
"The previous section introduced the Hopfield network as a dynamical "
"system whose state evolves to minimize an energy function. The weights of"
" the network determine the shape of this energy landscape, where the "
"valleys are located, how deep they are, and how steep the walls between "
"them. The question then arises: <b>how should these weights be set so "
"that the energy landscape encodes useful memories?</b> The answer lies in"
" a remarkably simple and biologically plausible principle proposed by "
"Canadian psychologist Donald Hebb in 1949. The <b>Hebbian learning "
"rule</b>, often summarized as <em>\"neurons that fire together, wire "
"together,\"</em> provides a local mechanism by which neural activity "
"sculpts the global energy function. This section explores the "
"mathematical connection between Hebbian synaptic modification and the "
"shaping of an energy landscape, establishing the foundational learning "
"principle that carries forward into the Boltzmann machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:15
msgid "<b>The Hebbian Postulate</b>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:17
msgid ""
"In his seminal work \"<em>The Organization of Behavior\"</em>, Hebb "
"proposed that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:19
msgid ""
"\"When an axon of cell A is near enough to excite cell B and repeatedly "
"or persistently takes part in firing it, some growth process or metabolic"
" change takes place in one or both cells such that A's efficiency, as one"
" of the cells firing B, is increased.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:21
msgid ""
"Translated into the language of artificial neural networks, this becomes "
"a simple weight update rule: if two connected neurons are simultaneously "
"active, the strength of their connection should increase. Conversely, if "
"their activities are anti-correlated, the connection strength should "
"decrease."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:23
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For binary neurons taking values in $\\{-1, +1\\}$, the change in weight "
"$w_{ij}$ due to a single pattern $\\boldsymbol{\\xi}$ is proportional to "
"the product of their activities:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:25
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\Delta w_{ij} \\propto \\xi_i \\xi_j"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:27
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For $\\{0, 1\\}$ valued neurons, a common variant adjusts weights only "
"when both neurons are active:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:29
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\Delta w_{ij} \\propto x_i x_j"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:31
msgid ""
"In both formulations, the essential principle is the same: <b>co-"
"activation strengthens the connection</b>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:33
msgid "<b>Storing Multiple Patterns: The Outer Product Rule</b>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:35
msgid ""
"To store a set of $P$ patterns $\\{\\boldsymbol{\\xi}^1, "
"\\boldsymbol{\\xi}^2, \\ldots, \\boldsymbol{\\xi}^P\\}$, the Hebbian "
"prescription is simply to sum the outer products of each pattern:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:37
#, python-brace-format
msgid "w_{ij} = \\frac{1}{N} \\sum_{\\mu=1}^P \\xi_i^\\mu \\xi_j^\\mu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:39
msgid ""
"The factor $1/N$ (or sometimes $1/P$ is a normalization constant that "
"prevents weights from growing without bound as more patterns are added. "
"The weight matrix can be written compactly as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:41
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\mathbf{W} = \\frac{1}{N} \\sum_{\\mu=1}^P \\boldsymbol{\\xi}^\\mu "
"(\\boldsymbol{\\xi}^\\mu)^\\top - \\frac{P}{N} \\mathbf{I}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:43
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"where the subtraction of the identity matrix enforces the condition "
"$w_{ii} = 0$ (no self-connections)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:45
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"This learning rule is purely <b>local</b>: to update $w_{ij}$, only the "
"activities of neurons $i$ and $j$ are required. No global error signal, "
"no backpropagation of gradients, no explicit knowledge of the energy "
"function is necessary. Yet, as we shall see, this local rule has a "
"profound global effect on the energy landscape."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:47
msgid "<b>Hebbian Learning as Energy Basin Creation</b>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:49
msgid ""
"Consider the energy function of the Hopfield network with Hebbian "
"weights. Substituting the outer product weight formula into the energy "
"definition yields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:51
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\begin{aligned}E(\\mathbf{x}) &= -\\frac{1}{2} \\sum_{i \\neq j} w_{ij} "
"x_i x_j - \\sum_i b_i x_i \\\\&= -\\frac{1}{2N} \\sum_{\\mu=1}^P \\sum_{i"
" \\neq j} \\xi_i^\\mu \\xi_j^\\mu x_i x_j - \\sum_i b_i x_i\\end{aligned}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:53
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For a state $\\mathbf{x}$ that exactly matches one of the stored "
"patterns, say $\\boldsymbol{\\xi}^\\nu$, the double sum simplifies "
"dramatically. Assuming the patterns are random and uncorrelated, the "
"dominant contribution comes from the term $\\mu = \\nu$:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:55
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\sum_{i \\neq j} \\xi_i^\\nu \\xi_j^\\nu \\xi_i^\\nu \\xi_j^\\nu = "
"\\sum_{i \\neq j} (\\xi_i^\\nu)^2 (\\xi_j^\\nu)^2 = N(N-1) \\approx N^2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:57
msgid "Thus, the energy of a stored pattern is approximately:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:59
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"E(\\boldsymbol{\\xi}^\\nu) \\approx -\\frac{1}{2N} \\cdot N^2 = "
"-\\frac{N}{2}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:61
msgid ""
"This is a <b>deep energy minimum</b>. In contrast, a random state "
"uncorrelated with any stored pattern will have energy near zero, because "
"the cross terms average out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:63
msgid ""
"The Hebbian rule therefore accomplishes the following geometric "
"transformation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:65
msgid ""
"<b>Basins of attraction</b> are carved into the energy landscape at the "
"locations of the stored patterns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:66
msgid ""
"The <b>depth</b> of each basin is proportional to $N$, the number of "
"neurons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:67
msgid ""
"The <b>walls</b> between basins are shaped by the crosstalk terms from "
"other patterns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:69
msgid ""
"In this precise sense, <b>Hebbian learning sculpts the energy "
"landscape</b>. Each memory contributes a quadratic depression centered at"
" the pattern vector. The collective effect of all stored memories is an "
"additive superposition of these depressions, resulting in a rugged "
"landscape whose local minima correspond, ideally, to the stored memories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:71
msgid "<b>The Mathematical Foundation for Hebb's Rule</b>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:73
msgid ""
"While Hebb's postulate is biologically motivated, the Boltzmann machine "
"provides a rigorous mathematical justification for it. Recall from "
"Section [3.1 Defining the Objective: Low Energy for Real Data](/kpp-"
"theoretical-foundations\\kpp-theoretical-foundations-ebms-def) the "
"gradient of the  log-likelihood for a Boltzmann machine:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:75
msgid ""
"\\frac{\\partial f}{\\partial w_{ij}} = \\langle x_i x_j "
"\\rangle_{\\text{data}} - \\langle x_i x_j \\rangle_{\\text{model}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:77
msgid ""
"This learning rule, often called the <b>contrastive Hebbian rule</b>, is "
"a direct generalization of Hebb's original idea. The first term, "
"$\\langle x_i x_j \\rangle_{\\text{data}}$, is purely <b>Hebbian</b>: it "
"strengthens the connection between two units when they are co-active in "
"the data. The second term, $\\langle x_i x_j \\rangle_{\\text{model}}$, "
"is <b>anti-Hebbian</b>: it weakens connections that are spuriously co-"
"active in the model's own generated fantasies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:79
msgid ""
"As derived in Section [3.3 Contrastive Divergence](/kpp-theoretical-"
"foundations\\kpp-theoretical-foundations-ebms-cd), the stochastic "
"gradient update for a Boltzmann machine can be written as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:81
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\Delta w_{ij} = \\eta \\left( X_i(\\omega) X_j(\\omega) - "
"\\mathbb{E}_\\theta [X_i X_j] \\right)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:83
msgid ""
"This formulation reveals that <b>the simple, local Hebbian update (\"fire"
" together, wire together\") emerges naturally from the principled "
"objective of maximizing the data likelihood</b>. In essence, the "
"Boltzmann machine's learning algorithm proves that Hebb's rule is not "
"just a biological heuristic but the optimal learning strategy when the "
"goal is to match the model's equilibrium distribution to the data "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:85
msgid "<b>Limitations of Hebbian Learning</b>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:87
msgid ""
"While elegant and biologically motivated, pure Hebbian learning has "
"significant drawbacks when used in Hopfield networks:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:89
msgid ""
"<b>Spurious Minima</b>: The crosstalk between stored patterns creates "
"unintended energy minima, mixture states and random valleys, that trap "
"dynamics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:90
msgid ""
"<b>Storage Capacity</b>: The number of patterns that can be reliably "
"stored scales only linearly with $N$, with a proportionality constant of "
"approximately 0.14. Beyond this, the network undergoes a phase transition"
" to a spin-glass state where no patterns are retrievable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:91
msgid ""
"<b>Catastrophic Forgetting</b>: Storing a new pattern modifies all "
"weights and can destabilize previously stored memories. There is no "
"mechanism to protect old memories while learning new ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:92
msgid ""
"<b>No Unlearning of Spurious States</b>: Once a spurious minimum is "
"created, pure Hebbian learning offers no way to eliminate it. The rule "
"only adds basins; it never fills them in.These limitations motivated the "
"development of more sophisticated learning algorithms, including the "
"<b>Boltzmann machine learning rule</b>, which uses a combination of "
"Hebbian and anti-Hebbian updates guided by the difference between data-"
"driven and model-driven correlations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:94
msgid "<b>From Hebbian Storage to Probabilistic Learning</b>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:96
msgid ""
"The Boltzmann machine inherits the energy-based architecture of the "
"Hopfield network and the idea that learning corresponds to modifying the "
"energy landscape. However, it replaces the simple Hebbian storage "
"prescription with a <b>principled probabilistic learning algorithm</b>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:98
msgid ""
"In a Boltzmann machine, the goal is not merely to store a set of patterns"
" as attractors, but to make the equilibrium distribution of the network "
"match the distribution of the observed data. The learning rule that "
"achieves this is a generalization of Hebb's principle:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:100
msgid ""
"\\Delta w_{ij} \\propto \\langle x_i x_j \\rangle_{\\text{data}} - "
"\\langle x_i x_j \\rangle_{\\text{model}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:102
msgid ""
"This is sometimes called the <b>contrastive Hebbian rule</b> or <b>delta "
"rule</b>. The first term, $\\langle x_i x_j \\rangle_{\\text{data}}$, is "
"the average correlation between units $i$ and $j$when the visible units "
"are clamped to data examples. This term is <b>Hebbian</b>: it strengthens"
" connections between units that are co-active in the data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:104
msgid ""
"The second term, $ \\langle x_i x_j \\rangle_{\\text{model}}$, is the "
"average correlation when the network runs freely from its own equilibrium"
" distribution. This term is <b>anti-Hebbian</b>: it weakens connections "
"that are spuriously co-active in the model's own fantasies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:106
msgid ""
"The difference between these two correlations drives the weight update. "
"If the data shows a stronger correlation than the model's current "
"distribution, the weight increases (lowering energy for that co-"
"activation pattern). If the model overestimates the correlation, the "
"weight decreases (raising energy for that pattern)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:108
msgid ""
"This contrastive update dynamically sculpts the energy landscape to match"
" the data distribution. It retains the local, Hebbian character of the "
"update—only the activities of the connected neurons are required—while "
"providing a principled way to avoid the pitfalls of pure Hebbian storage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:110
msgid "<b>Sculpting Energy: A Unifying Metaphor</b>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:112
msgid ""
"The metaphor of <b>sculpting an energy landscape</b> provides a powerful "
"unifying framework for understanding both Hopfield networks and Boltzmann"
" machines:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:114
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"<b>Weights as sculpting tools</b>: Each weight $w_{ij}$ acts like a "
"chisel that can either carve a valley (if $w_{ij} > 0$) or raise a ridge "
"(if $w_{ij} < 0$) along the diagonal where $x_i = x_j$."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:115
msgid ""
"<b>Hebbian learning as an additive process</b>: Each stored pattern adds "
"a new depression to the landscape, creating a new attractor basin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:116
msgid ""
"<b>Boltzmann learning as a corrective process</b>: By comparing data "
"correlations to model correlations, the learning algorithm not only adds "
"basins where data lies but also <b>fills in spurious basins </b>that the "
"model has invented."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:118
msgid ""
"This energy-centric view will recur throughout the remainder of this "
"tutorial. The restricted Boltzmann machine (RBM), deep belief networks, "
"and even modern energy-based models all share this <b>fundamental "
"perspective</b>: learning is the process of shaping an energy function so"
" that desirable configurations are assigned low energy and undesirable "
"configurations are assigned high energy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:120
msgid "<b>Summary</b>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:122
msgid ""
"<b>Hebbian learning</b> is a local, biologically plausible rule: "
"<em>neurons that fire together, wire together</em>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:123
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For binary patterns, the Hebbian weight update is $ \\Delta w_{ij} "
"\\propto x_i x_j$."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:124
msgid ""
"Storing multiple patterns corresponds to summing their outer products, "
"resulting in a weight matrix that reflects pairwise correlations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:125
msgid ""
"<b>Hebbian learning sculpts the energy landscape</b> by creating basins "
"of attraction at the locations of stored patterns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:126
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"A single weight increase $\\Delta w_{ij} > 0$ lowers the energy of states"
" where $x_i$ and $x_j$ agree and raises the energy where they disagree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:127
msgid ""
"Pure Hebbian learning suffers from <b>spurious minima</b>, <b>limited "
"capacity</b>, and <b>catastrophic forgetting</b>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:128
msgid ""
"The <b>Boltzmann machine learning rule</b> generalizes Hebb's principle "
"by subtracting model correlations from data correlations, providing a "
"principled way to shape the energy landscape to match a probability "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/kpp-theoretical-foundations/kpp-theoretical-foundations-nn-learning.md:129
msgid ""
"The metaphor of <b>energy sculpting</b> unifies the learning principles "
"of Hopfield networks and Boltzmann machines, and extends to modern deep "
"generative models."
msgstr ""

